label.value: regulation of metanephric cap mesenchymal cell proliferation

definition.value: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate, or extent of metanephric cap mesenchymal cell proliferation. Metanephric cap mesenchymal cell proliferation is the multiplication or reproduction of metanephric cap mesenchymal cells, resulting in the expansion of the cell population. A metanephric cap mesenchymal cell is a mesenchymal cell that has condensed with other mesenchymal cells surrounding the ureteric bud tip.

label.value: positive regulation of metanephric cap mesenchymal cell proliferation

definition.value: Any process that increases the frequency, rate, or extent of metanephric cap mesenchymal cell proliferation. Metanephric cap mesenchymal cell proliferation is the multiplication or reproduction of metanephric cap mesenchymal cells, resulting in the expansion of the cell population. A metanephric cap mesenchymal cell is a mesenchymal cell that has condensed with other mesenchymal cells surrounding the ureteric bud tip.
The polysaccharide-based coating on the inner side of a lysosomal membrane that protects it from digestion by lysosomal enzymes.

Any process that modulates the rate, frequency or extent of spindle assembly. Spindle assembly is the aggregation, arrangement and bonding together of a set of components to form the spindle, the array of microtubules and associated molecules that serves to move duplicated chromosomes apart.

label.value: microtubule cytoskeleton organization involved in synapsis

definition.value: A process that is carried out at the cellular level which results in the assembly, arrangement of constituent parts, or disassembly of cytoskeletal structures comprising microtubules and their associated proteins that contributes to chromosomal pairing.

Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of synaptonemal complex assembly. Synaptonemal complex assembly is the cell cycle process in which the synaptonemal complex, a structure that holds paired chromosomes together during prophase I of meiosis and that promotes genetic recombination, is formed.

label.value: chromosome localization to nuclear envelope involved in synapsis

definition.value: The directed movement of a chromosome to the nuclear envelope that contributes to synapsis.
Any process that modulates the rate, frequency or extent of the assembly, arrangement of constituent parts, or disassembly of the microtubule spindle.
Any process that modulates the number of microtubules in a given region of the spindle.

Any process that modulates the rate, frequency, or extent of the spindle checkpoint, a cell cycle checkpoint that delays the metaphase|anaphase transition until the spindle is correctly assembled and oriented, and chromosomes are attached to the spindle.

Any process that increases the rate, frequency, or extent of the spindle checkpoint, a cell cycle checkpoint that delays the metaphase|anaphase transition until the spindle is correctly assembled and oriented, and chromosomes are attached to the spindle.

Any process that decreases the rate, frequency, or extent of the spindle checkpoint, a cell cycle checkpoint that delays the metaphase|anaphase transition until the spindle is correctly assembled and oriented, and chromosomes are attached to the spindle.

label.value: cell proliferation involved in imaginal disc-derived wing morphogenesis

definition.value: The multiplication or reproduction of cells, resulting in the expansion of a cell population that contributes to imaginal disc-derived wing morphogenesis.

label.value: regulation of cell proliferation involved in imaginal disc-derived wing morphogenesis

definition.value: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate, or extent of the multiplication or reproduction of cells, resulting in the expansion of a cell population that contributes to imaginal disc-derived wing morphogenesis.

label.value: regulation of mitotic cell cycle spindle assembly checkpoint

definition.value: Any process that modulates the rate, frequency, or extent of the mitotic cell cycle spindle assembly checkpoint, a cell cycle checkpoint that delays the metaphase|anaphase transition of a mitotic nuclear division until the spindle is correctly assembled and chromosomes are attached to the spindle.

label.value: positive regulation of mitotic cell cycle spindle assembly checkpoint

definition.value: Any process that increases the rate, frequency, or extent of the mitotic cell cycle spindle assembly checkpoint, a cell cycle checkpoint that delays the metaphase|anaphase transition of a mitotic nuclear division until the spindle is correctly assembled and chromosomes are attached to the spindle.

label.value: activation of mitotic cell cycle spindle assembly checkpoint

definition.value: Any process that starts the inactive process of a mitotic cell cycle spindle assembly checkpoint.

label.value: positive regulation of transcription involved in G2|M transition of mitotic cell cycle

definition.value: Any process that activates or increases the frequency, rate or extent of transcription of target genes that are transcribed as part of the G2|M transition of the mitotic cell cycle.
Any process that modulates the rate, frequency, or extent of the multiplication or reproduction of osteoclasts, resulting in the expansion of an osteoclast cell population.
Any process that increases the rate, frequency, or extent of the multiplication or reproduction of osteoclasts, resulting in the expansion of an osteoclast cell population.
Any process that decreases the rate, frequency, or extent of the multiplication or reproduction of osteoclasts, resulting in the expansion of an osteoclast cell population.
Any process that modulates the rate, frequency or extent of the process in which new strands of DNA are synthesized in the mitochondrion.

label.value: positive regulation of mitochondrial DNA replication

definition.value: Any process that increases the rate, frequency or extent of the process in which new strands of DNA are synthesized in the mitochondrion.

label.value: negative regulation of mitochondrial DNA replication

definition.value: Any process that decreases the rate, frequency or extent of the process in which new strands of DNA are synthesized in the mitochondrion.
A ubiquitin-protein ligase activity that increases the rate or extent of the metaphase to anaphase transition of the mitotic cell cycle.
The aggregation, arrangement and bonding together of a set of components to form the spindle that contributes to the process of meiosis.
The aggregation, arrangement and bonding together of a set of components to form the spindle that contributes to the process of mitosis.

Any process that modulates the rate, frequency, or extent of DNA-dependent DNA replication, the process in which new strands of DNA are synthesized, using parental DNA as a template for the DNA-dependent DNA polymerases that synthesize the new strands.
Stops, prevents or reduces the activity of a polygalacturonase. Polygalacturonases catalyze the random hydrolysis of 1,4-alpha-D-galactosiduronic linkages in pectate and other galacturonans.
Stops, prevents, or reduces ornithine carbamoyltransferase activity, the catalysis of the reaction -  carbamoyl phosphate + L-ornithine -eq- phosphate + L-citrulline.

label.value: secondary cell wall biogenesis involved in seed trichome differentiation

definition.value: A cellular process that results in the biosynthesis of constituent macromolecules, assembly, and arrangement of constituent parts of inextensible cellulose- and pectin-containing cell walls that are formed between the plasma membrane and primary cell wall of seed trichomes after cell expansion is complete.
A cell projection that is a short, rounded projection from a plant epidermal cell.
A plant cell papilla that is part of a leaf papilla cell.
A plant cell papilla that is part of a stigma papilla cell.
The region at growing end of the pollen tube cell, where polarized growth occurs.
A cell projection part that is a branch of a unicellular trichome.
A tubular cell projection that is part of a pollen tube cell and extends from a pollen grain.
Catalysis of the reaction -  malonate + ATP + coenzyme A -eq- malonyl-CoA + AMP + diphosphate.
Interacting selectively and non-covalently with a brassinosteroid.
Catalysis of the reaction -  7-hydroxymethyl chlorophyll a + 2 reduced ferredoxin + 2 H+ chlorophyll a + 2 oxidized ferredoxin + H2O.
Enables the directed movement of nicotinate into, out of or within a cell, or between cells.
Enables the directed movement of N-methylnicotinate into, out of or within a cell, or between cells.

label.value: negative regulation of transcription involved in G2|M transition of mitotic cell cycle

definition.value: Any process that inhibits or decreases the frequency, rate or extent of transcription of target genes that are transcribed as part of the G2|M transition of the mitotic cell cycle.
Enables the directed movement of thiamine pyrophosphate into, out of or within a cell, or between cells.
Any process that starts the inactive process of meiosis.
Catalysis of the reaction -  caffeoyl-CoA + a saturated primary alcohol -eq- an alkyl caffeate + CoA.
Catalysis of the reaction -  ATP + myristic acid + CoA -eq- AMP + diphosphate + myristoyl-CoA.
Catalysis of the reaction -  ATP + palmitic acid + CoA -eq- AMP + diphosphate + palmitoyl-CoA.
Catalysis of the reaction -  ATP + oleic acid + CoA -eq- AMP + diphosphate + oleoyl-CoA.
Catalyzes the reaction -  (3S)-2,3-epoxy-2,3-dihydrosqualene -eq- camelliol C.
